        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 1:42PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 142 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 3
miles south of Saint Onge, or 5 miles east of Spearfish, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Spearfish, Whitewood, Nisland, Saint Onge, and Vale.

This includes Interstate 90 in South Dakota between Mile Markers 14
and 25.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

This storm is producing large quantities of hail. Driving through
deep hail is like driving on slushy roads. Slow down and do not brake
suddenly.</instruction>
